10W_QHgCA__TJPhhX-IfmD9zOgLPJcVPaEZFY9ki_sh8skKRxfmnV3NfEEuLczvTsaHhf3ikrjIYgSUtOt36OOjxxdNI30NDUS4Ffr6g==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing hadoop-client-runtime**\\n\\nI’m thinking that we might not need extensive inspection for the hadoop-client-runtime 3.3.1, since it includes shaded dependencies under specific packages. It has components like Apache Curator and Jetty, along with relocated dependencies. I wonder if a test for shaded Apache Commons Configuration would be beneficial. The runtime jar likely has the core Hadoop classes, and we might consider new features like shaded Jackson YAML. I'll need to ensure everything compiles correctly. I'll look deeper into the included shaded packages.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring commons-compress features**\\n\\nI'm noticing that the Commons Compress tar/zip functionality may be useful and doesn't present dynamic issues. I need to compile imports from the exact shaded package, specifically `org.apache.hadoop.shaded.org.apache.commons.compress.archivers.tar`. I believe hadoop-client-runtime 3.3.1 includes commons-compress, as Hadoop common depends on it. I should check the package path to confirm. Alternatively, I could consider using commons-cli for simplicity, but it may not offer all the needed functionality. I’ll analyze existing coverage and identify necessary features for testing.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating archive methods**\\n\\nI’m looking into using the commons-compress version in Hadoop 3.3.1 for working with Tar archives. It seems I need methods like creating a TarArchiveOutputStream and setting up TarArchiveEntries. There’s also a need to read from TarArchiveInputStream, but I wonder if methods like getNextTarEntry are deprecated in newer versions. The user prefers avoiding deprecated APIs, so I’ll confirm if methods like getNextEntry return the necessary entries without issues. I'll check how best to manage imports and streamline the process.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering archive management**\\n\\nI’m thinking about using ByteStreams as a helper tool for archive compression, but I need to ensure the logic flow isn't duplicated. I could add two entries, including a directory entry, which I’ll need to assert. For the TarArchiveEntry representing the directory, I wonder if I should use a constructor with a trailing slash and if I need to set its size. Also, ensuring the top-level class is public while keeping test methods package-private might work well. I’ll need to make some edits to clarify this.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_o8YHHSeGiEpwO1MqmhcQdmml|fc_004ec30417fd40fc0169fec4df2d44819ea31430567cdffe0d", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.hadoop/hadoop-client-runtime/3.3.1/src/test/java/org_apache_hadoop/hadoop_client_runtime/Hadoop_client_runtimeTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import org.apache.hadoop.shaded.org.apache.commons.codec.binary.Base64;\nimport org.apache.hadoop.shaded.org.apache.commons.codec.binary.Hex;\nimport org.apache.hadoop.shaded.org.apache.commons.codec.digest.DigestUtils;\nimport org.apache.hadoop.shaded.org.apache.commons.math3.linear.Array2DRowRealMatrix;", "newText": "import org.apache.hadoop.shaded.org.apache.commons.codec.binary.Base64;\nimport org.apache.hadoop.shaded.org.apache.commons.codec.binary.Hex;\nimport org.apache.hadoop.shaded.org.apache.commons.codec.digest.DigestUtils;\nimport org.apache.hadoop.shaded.org.apache.commons.compress.archivers.ArchiveEntry;\nimport org.apache.hadoop.shaded.org.apache.commons.compress.archivers.tar.TarArchiveEntry;\nimport org.apache.hadoop.shaded.org.apache.commons.compress.archivers.tar.TarArchiveInputStream;\nimport org.apache.hadoop.shaded.org.apache.commons.compress.archivers.tar.TarArchiveOutputStream;\nimport org.apache.hadoop.shaded.org.apache.commons.math3.linear.Array2DRowRealMatrix;"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void shadedCommonsMathComputesStatisticsAndSolvesLinearSystems() {\n        DescriptiveStatistics movingWindow = new DescriptiveStatistics(3);", "newText": "    @Test\n    void shadedCommonsCompressCreatesAndReadsTarArchives() throws IOException {\n        byte[] stdout = \"container started\\ncontainer stopped\\n\".getBytes(UTF_8);\n        ByteArrayOutputStream archive = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n\n        try (TarArchiveOutputStream output = new TarArchiveOutputStream(archive)) {\n            TarArchiveEntry entry = new TarArchiveEntry(\"logs/application/stdout\");\n            entry.setSize(stdout.length);\n            output.putArchiveEntry(entry);\n            output.write(stdout);\n            output.closeArchiveEntry();\n            output.finish();\n        }\n\n        try (TarArchiveInputStream input = new TarArchiveInputStream(new ByteArrayInputStream(archive.toByteArray()))) {\n            ArchiveEntry entry = input.getNextEntry();\n            byte[] restored = ByteStreams.toByteArray(input);\n\n            assertThat(entry).isNotNull();\n            assertThat(entry.getName()).isEqualTo(\"logs/application/stdout\");\n            assertThat(entry.isDirectory()).isFalse();\n            assertThat(entry.getSize()).isEqualTo(stdout.length);\n            assertThat(restored).isEqualTo(stdout);\n            assertThat(input.getNextEntry()).isNull();\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void shadedCommonsMathComputesStatisticsAndSolvesLinearSystems() {\n        DescriptiveStatistics movingWindow = new DescriptiveStatistics(3);"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 511, "output": 1637, "cacheRead": 11776, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 13924, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778304202225, "responseId": "resp_004ec30417fd40fc0169fec4caadac819eba1e7d54bcde87a9"}}
